A FEW GIT COMMANDS:

git init   : initiates the git repo, which is local repo

git stages/ git architecture
-----------------------------

workspace: where developers write the code. here the code will be in untracked stage.
           command to use to keep the records in tracking area is git add 

staging area:  here the code will be in tracked stage.
               command to use : git commit -m "commit message"

repository : all the tracked code will be stored in a repository.
             command to use : git push

